license: MIT
version: "1.0.0-simulation"
date-released: "2026-06-06"
year: 2026
keywords:
  - hallucination
  - selective inference
  - entropy
  - LLM
  - abstention
  - no fine-tuning
abstract: >
  DED (Differentiated-Equalized-Re-differentiated) is a lightweight
  inference wrapper that uses Shannon entropy over top-k logits to
  detect uncertainty and trigger structured abstention in LLMs —
  without fine-tuning or external retrieval.
notes: >
  Preliminary results based on simulated distributions
  (TruthfulQA N=817). GPU validation on Mistral-7B-Instruct-v0.3
  in progress.